            <title>[DERBY-2259] DatabaseMetaData.getTypeInfo() SEARCHABLE column returns incorrect information for types that cannot be searched.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-2259</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;These types cannot be searched (I think) and should have the value DatabaseMetaData.typePredNone&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Types.LONGVARBINARY returns DatabaseMetaData.typePredBasic&lt;br/&gt;
Types.LONGVARCHAR returns DatabaseMetaData.typeSearchable&lt;br/&gt;
Types.BLOB returns DatabaseMetaData.typePredChar;&lt;br/&gt;
Types.CLOB returns DatabaseMetaData.typePredChar;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
