                            <comment id="12468611" author="sv204098" created="Tue, 30 Jan 2007 13:46:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Linking this issue to Derby-2258 (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-2258&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-2258&lt;/a&gt;) as it is solved by the same patch which is available for that. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;JDK 6 API says for SEARCHABLE field for data types as follows : &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SEARCHABLE short =&amp;gt; can you use &quot;WHERE&quot; based on this type:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;typePredNone - No support&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;typePredChar - Only supported with WHERE .. LIKE&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;typePredBasic - Supported except for WHERE .. LIKE&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;typeSearchable - Supported for all WHERE ..&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;So I modified the values to 0 for LONGVARBINARY, LONGVARCHAR, CLOB, BLOB.&lt;br/&gt;
Also for the XML data type, kept this value 0, Is this correct ?&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12468982" author="knutanders" created="Wed, 31 Jan 2007 10:56:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LONG VARCHAR and CLOB support WHERE...LIKE, so they should return typePredChar.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ij version 10.2&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; connect &apos;jdbc:derby:db&apos;;&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; create table t (x long varchar);&lt;br/&gt;
0 rows inserted/updated/deleted&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; insert into t values &apos;abc&apos;;&lt;br/&gt;
1 row inserted/updated/deleted&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; select * from t where x like &apos;a%&apos;;&lt;br/&gt;
X                                                                                                                               &lt;br/&gt;
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;br/&gt;
abc                                                                                                                             &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1 row selected&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; create table t2 (c clob);&lt;br/&gt;
0 rows inserted/updated/deleted&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; insert into t2 values cast(&apos;abc&apos; as clob);&lt;br/&gt;
1 row inserted/updated/deleted&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; select * from t2 where c like &apos;a%&apos;;&lt;br/&gt;
C                                                                                                                               &lt;br/&gt;
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;br/&gt;
abc                                                                                                                             &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1 row selected&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12468990" author="sv204098" created="Wed, 31 Jan 2007 11:07:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Knut, I &apos;ll modify the patch accordingly (along with the changes required, if any, for Derby-2258 &amp;amp; Derby-2260).&lt;br/&gt;
Apart, any Idea about XML date type for this, currently I had put it as typePredNone (I am not familiar with XML data type&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12469094" author="army" created="Wed, 31 Jan 2007 16:37:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; Apart, any Idea about XML date type for this, currently I had put it as typePredNone (I am not &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; familiar with XML data type)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;typePredNone is the correct value for XML.  One is not allowed to search an XML value directly.  The only way to search/query XML values is via use of the XMLEXISTS() or XMLQUERY() operators.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12470630" author="sv204098" created="Tue, 6 Feb 2007 16:28:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for Derby-2258 implements the modification required.&lt;br/&gt;
This involves correcting the SEARCHABLE values for different data types.&lt;br/&gt;
Modified metadata.properties to return appropriate values for LONGVARBINARY, LONGVARCHAR &amp;amp; BLOB. Corresponding to this change, modified the DatabaseMetaDataTest.java to expect the correct values.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
